The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

                                        Archives
                                                   Patty confirms 

           
	Bangalore: Switzerlands Patty Schnyder has confirmed her participation in the Bangalore Open 2008, the biggest tennis extravaganza in South and South East Asia. 
    
	Schnyder has 10 tour wins to her credit and is currently ranked 14th in the WTA rankings, Karnataka State Lawn Tennis Association said announcing her participation. 
    
	It is great to be part of Indias first Tier II tennis extravaganza in Bangalore, Schnyder said.Serena Williams has already confirmed her participation in the event. 
    
	The Bangalore Open will be held here from March 3 to 9. The event has total prize money of $600,000. 
     (PTI) 
                                                 
